'''Christopher Knight''' is an author who has written several books dealing with theories such as [[Pseudoscientific_metrology#366_geometry|366-degree geometry]] and the origins of [[Freemasonry]]. Knight appears in the two-part [[History (U.S. TV channel)|History Channel]] documentary ''[[Decoding the Past]]'' &ndash; "Mysteries of the Freemasons".

In an interview about the book ''Who Built the Moon?: 2005'' Knight stated that the moon is an artificial construction probably built by humans with a message in "[[base ten]] arithmetic so it looks as though it is directed to a ten digit species that is living on Earth right now - which seems to mean humans." He believes that it was created to make life on Earth possible, including humans, and that the most likely builders were humans of the future using time travel.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Who Built the Moon? - An Interview With Christopher Knight|journal=New Dawn|date=May–June 2006|issue=96|url=http://www.newdawnmagazine.com/articles/who-built-the-moon-an-interview-with-christopher-knight}}</ref>

